{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"cec81cb1-3694-48e5-bab0-8142cdcd3261","content":"Two things change with xUnit.net v3 + MTP:\n\n1. **`--filter` → `--treenode-filter`** — MTP doesn't use VSTest's filter syntax.\n2. **Syntax** — tree-node filters use glob paths + `[property]` brackets instead of `&`/`~` operators.\n\nYour old filter:\n```\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\nBecomes:\n```\ndotnet test --treenode-filter \"/**/*IntegrationTests*/**[Category=Smoke]\"\n```\n\n**How it maps:**\n\n| VSTest concept | MTP tree-node equivalent |\n|---|---|\n| `FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests` | `/**/*IntegrationTests*/**` (glob match on class name) |\n| `Category=Smoke` | `[Category=Smoke]` (trait in brackets) |\n| `&` (AND) | both conditions in the same expression |\n\nThe path hierarchy is `/<Assembly>/<Namespace.Class>/<Method>`, so `/**/*IntegrationTests*/**` matches any test method inside a class whose name contains `IntegrationTests`. The `[Category=Smoke]` bracket filters on the `Trait` value.\n\nNo code changes are needed — your `[Trait(\"Category\", \"Smoke\")]` attribute works the same in v3.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"06b65d0d-e4b7-46f7-a6b2-2afaa6d7c4d8","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is migrating from xUnit v2 to xUnit v3 with MTP (Microsoft.Testing.Platform). With MTP, the `--filter` syntax changes.\n\nKey differences:\n1. With VSTest (v2), the filter syntax uses `&` for AND and `|` for OR, with operators like `~` (contains), `=` (equals).\n2. With MTP, the filter syntax changes. The `--filter` flag uses a different expression syntax.\n\nFor xUnit v3 with MTP:\n- The executable is the test project itself (since `OutputType` is `Exe`)\n- You can run with `dotnet run` or `dotnet test`\n\n\n- MTP uses a tree node filter syntax with `/` path separators instead of VSTest's filter operators\n- Traits like `[Trait(\"Category\", \"Smoke\")]` still work the same way in xUnit v3\n- The command uses `--treenode-filter` with a format like `/<assembly>/<namespace>/<class>/<method>[<property>=<value>]` to match tests by their hierarchical path and properties\n- For example, filtering by both class name and trait would look like `/**/*IntegrationTests*/**[Category=Smoke]`, where the glob pattern matches the FQN path and brackets specify trait filters like `Category=Smoke`\n\nNow I'm realizing I should clarify the actual dotnet test command syntax — with MTP, the proper flag is `--treenode-filter` rather than the VSTest-style `--filter`, though recent versions might still accept `--filter` and translate it internally.","outputTokens":1402},"id":"ffb84c98-b3a4-426d-994d-b619f6455058","timestamp":"2026-04-07T14:23:55.624Z","parentId":"3100a3ad-e8cb-434d-b42c-6d84514e6f5e"}
